cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.RO, cs.MA 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper proposes a dirty paper coding scheme and information-theoretic uplink-downlink channel duality to extract the most weighted throughput of UAV empowered wireless systems. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper investigates the integration of UAV into wireless communication systems and proposes to use radio energy harvesting technology at the UAV to extend the lifetime of UAV empowered base station. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper deals with the control and optimization of UAV empowered wireless systems. 
4. cs.RO (Robotics): The paper deals with the use of UAVs in wireless communication systems, which falls under the domain of robotics. 
5. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems): The paper deals with the optimization of UAV empowered wireless systems, which can be considered as a multiagent system.
